+Guidelines](https://opensource.google.com/conduct/).
+
+## Development
+
+We use TypeScript and TSLint for linting. Before submitting a pull request, please make sure to:
+
+1. Run `yarn presubmit` to make sure everything passes
+2. Follow the existing code style
+3. Include tests for new functionality
+4. Update documentation as needed
+
+## Code Structure
+
+This repository contains multiple models, each in their own directory with their own:
+
+- `package.json` file
+- `README.md` with documentation
+- `src/` directory with source code
+- `dist/` directory for build output
+- `demo/` directory for sample usage
+- `test/` or `run_tests.ts` with tests
+
+## Repository Improvements
+
+We've made the following improvements to the repository:
+1. Updated TypeScript configurations to use modern features and stricter checks
+2. Improved linting rules for better code quality
+3. Updated package.json files with better version management
+4. Modernized CI/CD pipeline configurations
+5. Improved documentation readability and structure
+6. Standardized code style across all models
